<LP>
   MAGAZINES: Capital Cities Media Inc., a Capital Cities/ABC
Inc. unit, agreed to sell Travel Agent magazine to a
partnership led by Richard Friese, a travel-industry
publisher. Terms weren't disclosed.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   ESQUIRE: Hearst Corp. named Lee Eisenberg editor in chief
of a British edition of Esquire, to be launched in March. His
successor as editor of the U.S. Esquire hasn't been named.
Adam Moss, former editor of the defunct 7 Days and now a
consultant with Time Warner Inc., said he discussed the job
with Hearst executives. A Hearst insider said Mr. Moss was
among those being considered, as was Gregory Curtis, editor
of Texas Monthly.
                                                                                                       

   WHO'S NEWS: Donald De Line was named senior vice president
of production for Walt Disney Co.'s Touchstone Pictures. He
was president of production for Snowback Productions. David
Vogel, vice president of production for Walt Disney Pictures,
was promoted to senior vice president of production for the
unit.
